def: Attentive to examine probable effects and consequences of actswith a view to avoid danger or misfortune; prudent; circumspect;wary; watchful; as, a cautious general.Cautious feeling for another's pain. Byron.Be swift to hear; but cautious of your tongue. Watts.
Covered with wartlike elevations; tuberculate; warty;verrucous; as, a verrucose capsule.
The mucilaginous drupaceous fruit of two East Indian trees(Cordia Myxa, and C. latifolia), sometimes used medicinally inpectoral diseases.
The act or the state of possessing again.
See Ern, n. Sir W. Scott.
Capable of being alkalified, or converted into an alkali.
The doctrine of arts in general; such branches of learning asrespect the arts.
An old term for a vertical section of a building; -- calledalso sciagraphy. See Vertical section, under Section.
